Let me analyze the structure and provide the solution.

Analysis of the Main Target Image:
- The structure consists of 6 blocks total
- It has 4 red blocks forming a circular opening in the center
- 2 yellow rectangular blocks on the top and bottom
- The structure is symmetrical
- It has three layers: top yellow block, middle red blocks, bottom yellow block

Required blocks from the dictionary:
- Red blocks: Need pieces #1, #2, #3, and #4 to form the circular opening
- Yellow blocks: Need two horizontal blocks #9 or #10 (they appear identical)

Assembly order (building from bottom up):
{
    Step1: Move block with index 9 (bottom yellow horizontal block)
    Step2: Move block with index 1 (bottom-left red quarter circle)
    Step3: Move block with index 2 (bottom-right red quarter circle)
    Step4: Move block with index 3 (top-left red quarter circle)
    Step5: Move block with index 4 (top-right red quarter circle)
    Step6: Move block with index 10 (top yellow horizontal block)
}

This assembly order will create the exact structure shown in the target image, with the circular opening in the middle and the yellow blocks framing the top and bottom.
